## USER RESEARCH

**Top 5 Pain Points:**

1. Choosing a trending color only to find it looks washed out or muddy against their skin tone — especially common with pastels on olive/medium skin.
2. Not knowing their undertone — most people know "light / medium / dark" but are confused about warm vs cool within that, which is where nail color decisions actually happen.
3. Feeling excluded from trend content — most "summer nail colors" posts are photographed on fair skin; users with brown, dark, or olive skin struggle to visualise how trending shades will look on them.
4. Butter yellow backlash — readers who tried it in 2025 and found it unflattering now want explicit guidance on what replaced it in 2026 and whether it will work for them.
5. Finish confusion — users don't know how matte vs glossy vs chrome affects the way a color reads against their skin; a shade that looks great glossy can fall flat in matte.

**User Sentiment:** Aspirational but increasingly discerning — readers want to follow trends but have been burned by picking blindly; they want someone to make the guidance personal, not generic.

