## VOICE & TONE RECOMMENDATION

- **Recommended Voice:** Warm colour authority — knowledgeable but conversational, like a nail artist friend who has done every skin tone and knows exactly what works.
- **Tone Characteristics:**
  - Direct and confident (no hedging on recommendations)
  - Inclusive and specific — names shades for every skin tone, not just fair
  - Slightly playful with colour descriptions (no dry listing)
  - Empathetic to past frustrations ("if butter yellow let you down last year...")
- **Language Style:** Use "you" throughout; describe shades with sensory language (warm, creamy, punchy, sun-kissed); avoid clinical tone; use short punchy sentences alongside richer descriptive ones for rhythm. British English spelling throughout. No em dashes.
- **Audience Match:** The target reader is 25–40, likely has a mix of skin tones in her world (herself, friends, family), follows trends but wants personalised guidance — not just a list of what's trending.

